(44, 19, 27, 40, 23, 13, 13, 'whom all Asia and the world worshippeth', 'Worship and Hypocrisy Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of worship and the consequences of hypocrisy. In Acts, the worship of Diana is threatened, paralleling the condemnation of the Pharisees in Matthew for shutting others out of true worship.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 27, 44, 19, 21, 21, 'whom all Asia and the world worshippeth', 'Connection of Worship and Purpose', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of worship, with Acts 19:27 highlighting the worship of Diana and Acts 19:21 indicating Paul''s intent to spread the gospel. This connection highlights the clash between pagan worship and the Christian mission.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 27, 62, 5, 19, 19, NULL, 'World and Wickedness Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of the world''s opposition to God. In Acts, the worship of Diana represents a broader worldly wickedness, while 1 John explicitly states that the whole world lies in wickedness.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 27, 66, 13, 3, 3, 'whom all Asia and the world worshippeth', 'Worship and Worldly Influence', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of worship and its impact on society. In Acts, the worship of Diana is threatened, while in Revelation, the world marvels at the beast, indicating a shift in allegiance.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 28, 66, 13, 4, 4, 'Great is Diana of the Ephesians', 'Worship and Idolatry Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of worship in both passages. In Acts, the people exalt Diana, while in Revelation, they worship the beast, indicating a parallel in idolatrous devotion.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 28, 66, 17, 13, 13, 'Great is Diana of the Ephesians', 'Worship and Power Dynamics', 'This connection highlights the theme of collective fervor in worship, as seen in Acts where the crowd exclaims, ''Great is Diana of the Ephesians.'' Similarly, Revelation depicts a unified group giving their power to the beast, suggesting a parallel in how groups can rally around a central figure or ideology.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 28, 9, 5, 3, 5, 'Great is Diana of the Ephesians', 'Idolatry and Divine Supremacy', 'This connection highlights the theme of idolatry and the supremacy of the true God. In both passages, the worship of false gods, Diana and Dagon, is contrasted with the power of the Lord, leading to the downfall of these idols.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 28, 11, 18, 26, 29, 'Great is Diana of the Ephesians', 'Worship and False Gods', 'Both passages emphasize fervent worship of false gods. In Acts, the crowd''s cry of ''Great is Diana'' parallels the prophets of Baal''s desperate calls for their god''s attention in 1 Kings.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 28, 19, 2, 2, 2, NULL, 'Opposition to Divine Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of opposition to divine authority. In both passages, there is a collective outcry against what is perceived as a threat to their beliefs, whether it be the worship of Diana or the rebellion against the Lord and His anointed.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 28, 23, 41, 5, 7, NULL, 'Fear and Encouragement in Worship', 'This connection highlights the theme of fear and communal encouragement in response to worship. In Acts, the crowd''s wrath and declaration of ''Great is Diana'' reflects a fervent devotion similar to the encouragement seen in Isaiah, where individuals rally together in fear and support.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 28, 24, 50, 38, 38, 'Great is Diana of the Ephesians', 'Idolatry and Wrath Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the fervent devotion to idols, with Acts highlighting the wrath of the people for their goddess Diana, while Jeremiah speaks of madness for graven images. This connection highlights the consequences of idolatry and the emotional responses it elicits.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
